column5: Got out today for a little Lake Onario salmon fishing.    Caught everything in 30 feet of water.    Went 6/7 in the morning on body baits.
Great Job, some nice fish there.  That's a big brownie
Look at that gut on that brown. Good job
whats the emoticon for jealously drewling? Nice going!
Thats awesome Greg By any chance was there a lure stuck on one of them?
thats one that will bug me for a little while, its probably floating around by now lol
well done !!! some nice early spring lake o fish!!!
Is it true you can only eat them once a month due to the mercury levels?
Beauty fish!  Great job out there. Were you using riggers, lead, or flat-lining those body baits?
fishing with planer boards and long lining I'm not sure how many of them you can eat actually.  The small ones seem okay, younger fish.  more just for the excitement.
